                      <span>2001-08-20</span>
                    </div>
                    <span>I bought this book based on an article on feral cats which was written by Pam. Curious enough I decided to check her book and I bought. I have 3 cats and I thought I knew everything but I was wrong! The book cover all the topics a cat owner should know and I recommend it if you are thinking about getting a cat. <P>The medical appendix is extremly useful and gives a brief description about common cat diseases. Her appendix helped me to explain better to my vet about what was going one with one cat of mine who was sick.<P>The behaviour tips are very good, and Pam really explain the importance of using interactive toys with cats, and specially important how to keep the peace if your house has more than one cat. Also the chapter about the litter box is a must-read. Many concerns about location, how many and which kind of litter are all explained<P>If you think about getting a cat this book has a very comprehensive description of what to look for. Her tips involve not only good sense but also important aspects people should observe when getting a new cat. The part about the shelter is certainly the strongest part and very nice explained.<P>I strongly suggest this book, for new cat owners and for experienced cat owners. I have read at least 3 times and I still use as my personal reference.</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">With this book, you'll see the world through kitty's eyes!</div>
                    <div>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Rating: </span>
